SMS-Send-SMSGlobal-HTTP

SMS::Send::SMSGlobal::HTTP is an SMS::Send driver that delivers messages
via HTTP or HTTPS through the www.smsglobal.com/http-api.php gateway.

You will need to create a trial account, at http://smsglobal.com, before
using this driver.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc SMS::Send::SMSGlobal::HTTP

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=SMS-Send-SMSGlobal-HTTP

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/SMS-Send-SMSGlobal-HTTP

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/SMS-Send-SMSGlobal-HTTP

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/SMS-Send-SMSGlobal-HTTP/


